TLINE.TDLINE: &TITLE&
Provident Fund Reporting for RPFC (HINCEPF0)
&PURPOSE&
This function enables you to display and print reports that provide
detailed information on the employee and employer contributions to the
trust and lists the employees who would begin contributing towards
Provident Fund (PF) or discontinue to do so.
The data can be broken down according to user-defined search criteria
and grouped into key data that is displayed in the following reports:
Form 5 - Provides details of employees joining the Trust in the month
Form 10 - Provides details of employees leaving the Trust in the month
Form 12A - Combined statement of employee and employer contributions to
the Fund in the month
ECR - Provides Provident Fund and Pension details of the employee and
the employer for the specified month. Along with these, this report also
provides details of employees joining or leaving the Trust in the
specified month.
These reports are submitted to the Regional Provident Fund
Commissioner's office (RPFC) in the statutory format through which the
company reports the employee and employer's contribution details for
provident fund.
&INTEGRATION&
&PREREQUISITES&
You have to maintain the<LS> Provident Fund Contribution </>(0587)
infotype
You have run the payroll for your employees and have payroll results
&FEATURES&
The reports list detailed provident fund contribution details, employees
who join the fund or discontinue contributing depending on the form
selected.
<LS>Provident Fund Reporting</>
From within this report you can trigger three separate reports:
Form 5 for PF
The report displays the list of new employees who qualify to contribute
from the current payroll period, and displays the following data:
Employee number
Employee's provident fund number
Employee name
Employee's date of birth
Employee's date of joining the PF fund
Form 10 for PF
The report displays the list of employees who discontinue contributing
to PF from the current payroll period, and displays the following data:
Employee number
Employee's provident fund number
Employee name
Date of leaving
Reason for leaving
Form 12A for PF
The report displays the employee and employer contribution details with
the break down of the amounts and percentages contributed to Provident
Fund, PF administration, pension fund, Employee Deposit Linked Insurance
(EDLI) and EDLI administration and displays the following data:
Employee number
Employee's provident fund number
PF rate
Employee's PF contribution amount
Employer's PF contribution amount
PF administration charges
Employer's pension contribution
Employer's EDLI contribution
EDLI administration charges
ECR
This report displays Provident Fund and Pension details of the employee
and the employer for the specified month. Along with these, this report
also displays details of employees joining or leaving the Trust in the
specified month. The following fields are displayed on the ALV output
screen:
<LS>Employee Number</>
<LS>Employee Name</>
<LS>EPF Wages</> - Indicates the basis that the system uses to calculate
an employee's contribution towards provident fund.
<LS>EPS Wages </>- Indicates the basis that the system uses to calculate
the employer's contribution towards pension.
<LS>EPF Contribution Due</> - Indicates the amount that the employee is
due to contribute towards provident fund.
<LS>EPF Contribution Remitted </>- Indicates the amount that the
employee has remitted towards provident fund for the specified month.
<LS>EPS Contribution Due</> - Indicates the amount that the employer is
due to contribute towards pension.
<LS>EPS Contribution Remitted</> - Indicates the amount that the
employer has remitted towards pension for the specified month.
<LS>Difference EPF & EPS Contribution Due</> - Indicates the
difference between the employer's contribution to PF and pension, that
is due for payment for the specified month.
<LS>Difference EPF & EPS Contribution Remitted </>- Indicates the
difference between the employer's contribution to PF and pension,
already paid for the specified month.
<LS>NCP Days</> - Indicates the number of days in the month for which
wages are not due.
<LS>Refund of Advances</> - Indicates the amount that is repaid toward
PF incase, the employee had opted for partial withdrawal of funds. The
refund is made by the employer on behalf of the employee.
<LS>EPF Wages Arrears</> - Indicates the unpaid wages for PF from the
previous months.
<LS>Employee EPF Arrears</> - Indicates the contributions not made
towards employee PF in previous months.
<LS>Employer EPF Arrears</> - Indicates the contributions not made
towards employer PF in previous months.
<LS>Employer EPS Arrears</> - Indicates the contributions not made
towards employer pension in previous months.
<LS>Father/Husband Name</>
<LS>Father/Husband Flag</> - Indicates whether the name specified in the
previous field is that of the employee's father or husband. This field
can have the values <LS>F</> (father) or <LS>H</> (husband).
<LS>Date of Birth</>
<LS>Gender</>
<LS>Date of Joining EPF</> - Indicates the date on which the employee
joined the provident fund scheme.
<LS>Date of Joining EPS</> - Indicates the date on which the employee
joined the pension scheme.
<LS>Date of Leaving EPF</> - Indicates the date on which the employee
left the provident fund scheme.
<LS>Date of Leaving EPS</> - Indicates the date on which the employee
joined the pension scheme.
<LS>Reason for Leaving</> - Indicates the reason due to which the
employee left the provident fund scheme.
&SELECTION&
You set the payroll area and period for which the report is to be
generated in the following fields:
Payroll Area
Payroll Period
You can further restrict the employees selected by entering individual
or a range of:
Personnel no
Personnel Area
Personnel Subarea
Employee Subgroup
Payroll area
You must also enter the following information:
The 'Trust ID' to specify the localized branch of the trust where the
contribution is made.
Select the <LS>eFiling</> checkbox if you want the electronic challan to
be available for Provident Fund and Pension details.
&STANDARD_VARIANTS&
&OUTPUT&
The system generates a display list with the employees basic details
corresponding to the form that is selected.
A list of errors, if any.
The Form 5, 10 or 12A as selected.
&ACTIVITIES&
Choose Tools -> ABAP Workbench and click the ABAP Editor button to
access the ABAP editor window. You can also use the /se38 transaction to
access this window.
Enter the technical name of the report and execute.
Enter the selection criteria in the respective fields.
Select the report to be run in the <LS>Report name</> field.
Enter the details of the bank where the amount is deposited.
Enter the date to be printed on the report in the <LS>Report date</>
field.
In case you do not use the standard layout, click the <LS>Customer
Layout</> button, which enables you to enter an existing customized
layout form name.
Choose Program -> Execute.
&EXAMPLE&
Mr. Sanjay's employer makes their PF contributions to the RPFC trust in
Mumbai and Bangalore in the trust ID's RP01 and RP02 in the two cities
respectively.
When Mr. Sanjay relocated to Bangalore in the month of April, his
employer started contributing to the trust ID RP02 instead the former.
When the employer runs Form 5 in the month of May for the Trust ID RP02,
Mr. Sanjay is listed as he now starts contributing to the Trust ID RP02.
Similarly, running Form 10 for the Trust ID RP01 lists him as he has
stopped contributing.
Note
If no payroll results are found for the employee in the selected payroll
period or the employee's record is not present in the selected Trust Id
for any day of the period, then that employee is rejected.
